    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Distinctive type of opus sectile ("cut work") technique, by which small triangles and rectangles of colored stones and glass mosaics are set into stone matrices or encrusted upon stone surfaces of floors, walls, or church fixtures; particularly as used in works with geometric patterns produced in Rome from the 12th to the 14th centuries. The name derives from the surname of a family of marbleworkers active in Rome, although all works of this type were not made by this one family.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046691/Lucie-Smith, Thames &amp; Hudson Dictionary of Art Terms (1986)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079228/Grove Art Online (2008-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tipo de decoración en incrustaciones de mosaico y mármol, encontrado especificamente en Roma desde el siglo XII al XIV.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wordt gebruikt voor met mozaïek ingelegde marmeren architectuuronderdelen, die met name van de 12e tot de 14e eeuw in de kunst van Rome voorkomen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052398/Encyclopedie van de kunst (1969)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>特殊的切割工藝類型，方法是將小型的三角形與長方形彩色石頭及玻璃馬賽克圖案嵌裝於石製基體中，或是裝設於地板、牆壁或教堂設備的石製表面；特別用於指稱西元十二至十四世紀間，於羅馬所製作的幾何圖案工藝。其命名乃是源自活躍於羅馬的大理石工匠家族的姓氏，然而並非所有此類型的工藝都是由此家族所製作完成。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
